Some of the prevalent psychiatric disorders are anxiety and depression. Both disorders are more prevalent in women and in middle-aged people. However in the more recent times, more people in the early to mid 20s are being diagnosed with these conditions.There is also a link between depression and anxiety with those who live in crowded metropolitan cities. As depression is linked to low levels of serotonin, here could be a possible link to gradual degeneration of neurons and receptors as we grow older.


